      <section eId="sec_47_A">
        <num>47-A</num>
        <heading>Regulating the handling and sale of products made from recovered milk fat and solids</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_47_A__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>from mixtures of milk and potable water produced in the operation\nof high-temperature short-time pasteurizers or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_47_A__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>from rinsings or drippings recovered from cans or equipment used\nin the handling of milk and milk products, provided such rinsings or\ndrippings do not contain excessive foreign substance, or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_47_A__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>from whey or to use such fat and such other milk solids in\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_47_A__subsec_c__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>products in the manufacture of which milk fat, other milk solids\nand water are permitted ingredients, or\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_47_A__subsec_c__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>in the manufacture of butter and skimmed milk powder (nonfat\ndry-milk solids).\n  The commissioner is hereby authorized to promulgate regulations\ngoverning the handling, manufacturing and marketing of such mixtures,\nrinsings, drippings and whey and the products made therefrom, and may\nprescribe standards for such products.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
      </section>
